      <highlights>&lt;p&gt;There is an Avalanche Warning in affect for the western portion of the South San Juan zone, including the La Plata Mountains, Needle Mountains and the Grenadier Range. A large winter storm has increased the avalanche danger to HIGH (Level 4) on the western part of the Southern San Juan zone. Natural and human-triggered avalanches are likely. Backcountry travelers should avoid moving on or under slopes steeper than about 30 degrees.&lt;/p&gt;</highlights>
